social_posts.post_text: i didn’t post my 2021 wrapped because it barely changed from 2020. i was still suffering from massive insecurity with my project & the fear of the decline i was dealing with from the year prior. it felt like confirmation that i wasn’t growing. but i kept going. i pushed & worked harder than i ever imagined. this year, it doubled. i am so grateful for that. for any of you who found me this year to those that have known me a while, thank you for being here. if you’re a producer or an artist & you’re struggling, keep going. don’t stop. 😭💚 (P.S. loving my most shared lyric lol)

i turn 26 today. that feels so crazy to say. the last year has been a blur. this time last year, everything started finally piecing together in ways i could never imagine. it’s honestly so hard sometimes to actually stop & “smell the roses” - i’ve spent a lot of time in GO GO GO mode & not actually digesting or processing anything that’s happened. it’s finally hit me, i’m letting some of these wins actually sink in. i can’t believe this is where i am. so many “firsts” crossed off this year. so many amazing new people i’ve met. so many amazing opportunities to play for you. my dreams are coming true right before my eyes. i’ll be sure to live in the moment as much as i can. thank you for being here, & thank you for making this happen. you guys make me *really happy* i love you ❤️🎉

ONE YEAR OF LASERBEAM. well, since the release anyway. an entire year of my life being changed forever. no words will ever fully describe how incredibly grateful i am for what has happened since this song came out. i always get asked if i expected the song to be as big as it is, & i can honestly say i had no damn idea. i’ve been making music since 2010, this ray volpe project has been around since 2012. you can’t predict these things. i’ll never forget the first time i noticed y’all starting to scream “laser” - it was in montreal in april 2022. only two months after the track went viral, unreleased, & still two months before it had even come out. i was so caught off guard when i heard. y’all screaming it, i thought i was going crazy haha. the overwhelming amount of love & support y’all have shown me has been surreal. i got to play this song all over the world: america, canada, mexico, japan, thailand, belgium, france, australia, new zealand?! like what is that?!?! we hit the billboard charts with this, hell the song is in FORTNITE RADIO… that’s something i never expected to happen in my life. it’s crazy to say i had one of the biggest bass songs of the last year… every single idol i’ve looked up to all across the dance scene from excision to skrillex to afrojack, playing this song out… it’s been a dream come true times a million. not to mention how much this song ascended from just the bass scene. there’s a remix & version for every genre you can think of. it’s such a crazy thought to think that my song has been flipped by some of the greatest artists out there. i am so grateful man. to this day, it’s still somehow going strong as hell & making waves in ways i don’t understand. it’s forever part of history, i can’t believe i get to be part of it in some way. i’ll never get tired of this song, bring out the lasers forever ❤️

some people like to say numbers aren't important or that it's not a healthy thing to look at, but for me it's been a sign of growth over time that i really love to compare to & see that the hard work is really paying off. 

we are over double the stats from last year, which is absolutely mind blowing. to be able to conquer the biggest headache of all time which is "following up" or just continuing to grind after having a huge song is mentally draining, it's taken a huge toll on me. to be able to have songs like "happy song" or "eat sleep rage" take form & get similar amounts of love just fills me with such gratitude that i can't express. i also honestly get in my head all the time because my music is more "commercial/mainstream dubstep" (my own term lol) imo, i'm not making extremely heavy music nor extremely melodic music, i sit in this like digestible mix area (which i love that i do) but it's a lot harder to hit than it is to miss when it comes to success and not just kinda following exact trends in a certain way but merging them and doing things with a specific level of energy. idk i'm rambling now. i'm really grateful that something clicked & has started to work. thank you for listening, & thank you for being here ❤️

WE DID IT. WE JUST SOLD OUT MY HOMESTATE SHOWS IN NORTH CAROLINA. CHARLOTTE + RALEIGH. 

i was raised in charlotte, learned about edm here, i became an artist here. i’ve done so many support shows in the city, without ever doing my own headline. last night was my first ever headline in charlotte & we sold it out.

raleigh was actually the first venue i ever performed in for a little soft ticket headline weekly party back in 2015, no one knew who i was, i just was the guy for the night. to come back all these years later and sell out both of these, it means everything to me.

this weekend has been such a massive full circle moment that will stick with me forever. north carolina you are forever my home, even if i may not live there anymore. thank you for showing up for me, thank you for believing in me ❤️
